\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 [  Resist the urge to overplay the intensity of Maggie's initial feelings of anger, disappointment, or betrayal. These have no strong roots, and quickly transition to gratitude. The beginning of the scene is actually meant to be a little bit fun. Neither Laura or Evan are disappointed that and initially, play off in a way that should be seen as light humor to the reader. ]<!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 A jolt of realization shot through Maggie. "Why is there no postmark on this envelope?" The room seemed to spin around her as she tried to process this impossible discovery. Laura's breath hitched, and her hand fluttered nervously at her throat. Evan's eyes darted between Maggie and the envelope, his jaw tightening with a mix of resignation he was about to be exposed, and relief that he wouldn't have to deceive Maggie about the scholarship anymore.}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sl120\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::2>[  In the quest to cleverly craft the scene where Laura humorously declares, "It's got a stamp!" we aim to capture the comedic essence rooted in an earlier slip-up by Evan. This scene unfolds with Laura jesting about Evan's initial forgetfulness to affix a stamp on their meticulously planned scholarship envelope \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  a light-hearted jab at their collective clumsiness in executing the scholarship scheme. At this pivotal moment, Laura's declaration serves as a self-mocking acknowledgment of their oversight, while she subtly credits herself for remembering the stamp, albeit overlooking the crucial detail of a postal postmark. Her statement oscillates between self-amusement and a flicker of hope that Maggie might focus on the presence of the stamp as a sign of authenticity, brushing aside the glaring absence of a postmark. This blend of self-deprecation and optimistic persuasion is designed to invoke chuckles from the readers, highlighting the endearing, albeit flawed, efforts of Evan and Laura as they navigate through their well-intentioned conspiracy.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 ]<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sl120\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(tried to sound convincing):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s got a stamp!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Know something's not right, but still hasn't put it all together):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0   }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But it should have a postmark like all these other envelopes.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sl120\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::2>[  Evan realizes their scheme has been uncovered, and surprisingly, he feels a sense of relief. The burden of maintaining a lie about the scholarship throughout their relationship had been a heavy one. With a humorous tone, devoid of any irritation, he utters, "Damn, postmark." This line is delivered not out of frustration, but with a playful, lighthearted humor, aiming to elicit a chuckle from the readers. It's a moment that showcases Evan's ability to find amusement in the unraveling of their carefully laid plans, reflecting his easygoing nature. ]<!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Realizing the jig is up):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan knew the gig was up. Under his breath, he said, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Damn postmark.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Distressed as the situation becoming clearer):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, what did you do? Please tell me this is not from you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Evan knows that he's busted, but hopes his words will commence Maggie to just ignore the truth of the situation and accept the anonymity of the benefactor, even though at this point everybody knows that he is the benefactor.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The letter said the benefactor of the scholarship wishes to remain anonymous. I think we should honor that.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s answer did nothing to misdirect Maggie. Instead, she saw it as a clear validation that Evan was the benefactor.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Distressed):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, you know there is no way I can accept this.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Pleading tone):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why not?\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Now that Maggie's exposed the scheme, she seeks to know the details):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How did you know the exact amount I needed to finish school? I never even told you I was having problems paying tuition.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Maggie spotted the guilty expression on Laura\loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8217\'92s face ):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh no. Please don\u8217\'92t tell me you\u8217\'92re involved in this too?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Playfully tucked in her elbows, spread her hands out wide, smiled):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Meet the selection committee!\u8221\'94}
