\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Sincere and caring):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We just wanted to help you finish something so important to you.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Grateful, Her resolve weakened significantly, but still showing resistance):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s not that I don\u8217\'92t appreciate the offer and the effort from you both, but I simply can\u8217\'92t accept such a large amount of money. So, thank you, Evan, and thank you, Laura. But I am rejecting the scholarship. I want you to have your money back.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Neutrally stating a hard fact.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You can reject the scholarship if you want, but that money won\u8217\'92t come back to me. This scholarship is 100% legal and legitimate. If you don\u8217\'92t accept the scholarship, the money will have to go to another Irish American culinary student.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Shocked, her initial reaction to this fact is of being trapped or forced into accepting this gift.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re kidding me!?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Maximum pleading tone, With a touch of worry):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No, he\u8217\'92s not kidding. That money must go to a culinary student. Since I\u8217\'92m the sole member of the selection committee, I\u8217\'92ll have to pick someone else to receive the scholarship. Maggie, please don\u8217\'92t make me give that money to someone else.\u8220\'93}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Still in disbelief):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This is crazy!\u8221\'94 }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(She stood up and walked into the kitchen in a futile attempt to escape the situation.)<!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Laura motioned to Evan with her head to comfort Maggie. Evan hugged Maggie for several minutes while she cried. Eventually, she finished crying and gently pushed Evan away.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Her resolve, now on its final leg. Trying to come to terms with the situation.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t know how to be okay with this.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Laura looked at Evan as to ask him if it was time for the last-resort tactic. He nodded yes. So, Laura went for it.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Seeing Maggie's resolve at its weakest point, Laura's distrust turned optimism. It was time for them to implement their last-resort tactic.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I think you\u8217\'92re looking at this all wrong, Maggie. If the situation were reversed and Evan needed money to finish school, wouldn\u8217\'92t you give it to him? Wouldn\u8217\'92t you easily sacrifice two weeks of income to make such an important impact in his life?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Acknowledging the truth in Laura's statement, but exercising one last gasp of resistance.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of course, I would. You know I would. But it\u8217\'92s $15,000, Laura!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(speaking with more conviction, Applying more persuasive pressure):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Stop thinking of it like that. It\u8217\'92s one to two weeks of income Evan would earn if he sat on the beach the whole time. There is no reason for you not to accept this from him. And if everything were reversed, you\u8217\'92d insist he accept the money from you. Am I right or not?\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Evan pulled Maggie\loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8217\'92s face up by her chin and kissed her. Speaking in a soft, gentle, caring tone.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Please accept the scholarship. I want you to have it, and you deserve it.\u8221\'94}
